This paper deals with the optimization of spectrum leasing and pricing decisions in a dynamic game setting, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also considers the impact of wireless network characteristics on the leasing and pricing decisions, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the security and privacy issues related to dynamic spectrum leasing, which could be classified under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions the potential applications of dynamic spectrum leasing in multimedia communication systems, which could be relevant to the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
